# How to Run Main Project

## Quick Start
```bash
# 1. Setup environment
source venv/bin/activate
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-your-key-here"

# 2. Run main processor
python3 blog_processor.py --url "https://medium.com/article-url"

# 3. Use generated questions with Chrome extension
# File: processed_content/questions/*.questions.json
```

## Alternative Commands
```bash
# Process with custom output
python3 blog_processor.py --url "https://example.com/blog" --output-dir results

# Debug mode
python3 blog_processor.py --url "https://example.com/blog" --debug
```

## Chrome Extension Setup
1. Chrome → chrome://extensions/
2. Enable "Developer mode"
3. Load unpacked → Select chrome-extension/ folder
4. Upload .questions.json file and inject on any website

## Files Generated
- processed_content/summaries/{id}.summary.json
- processed_content/questions/{id}.questions.json ← Use this with extension

## MongoDB Integration (Optional)
# Start MongoDB for persistent storage
cd mongodb && ./scripts/mongodb_setup.sh start

# Access MongoDB
# Web Interface: http://localhost:8081 
#   Login: admin / password123
# Direct Connection: mongodb://admin:password123@localhost:27017/blog_ai_db
# Command Line: docker exec selflearning_mongodb mongosh -u admin -p password123

# Run MongoDB example
python mongodb_example.py

## Blog Processing Options

# Option 1: Store in files (original behavior)
./venv/bin/python blog_processor.py --url "https://medium.com/@alxkm/effective-use-of-threadlocal-in-java-applications-f4eb6a648d4a"

# Option 2: Store in MongoDB collections
./venv/bin/python blog_processor.py --url "https://medium.com/@alxkm/effective-use-of-threadlocal-in-java-applications-f4eb6a648d4a" --mongodb

# Option 3: Use dedicated MongoDB processor
./venv/bin/python blog_processor_mongodb.py --url "https://medium.com/@alxkm/effective-use-of-threadlocal-in-java-applications-f4eb6a648d4a"